<B><P>IC Award Guidelines:</P>
</B><P>Just a few points to clarify the amount of IC's you should award for different things.  When you reward the IC's you do it directly through the Holonet. Award each event individualy. Do not group all your weeks events together to add just the one IC amount.</P>

<OL>

<LI><B>Hunts</B>: For web, url, hth hunts use 30K for 1St, 20K for others correct, 10K for incorrect and 0IC's for wrong ID or no effort submissions.</LI>
<LI><B>Fiction</B>: When awarding for this type of work the amount will vary due to quality. The max award for the winner of the event is 75K.</LI>
<LI><B>Graphic</B>: When awarding for this type of work the amount will vary due to quality. The max award for the winner of the event is 75K.</LI>
<LI><B>Trivia</B>: Trivia will be awarded at 3K per correct answer. Trivia is to be in sets of questions no greater than 10.</LI>
</OL>

<B><P>Do’s &amp; Don’ts:</P>
</B><P>Just a few points to clarify anything that has not been covered. Some are just pointing out some rules which are though of as unspoken, and never really covered before.</P>
<OL>

<U><LI>Do</U> respect your Wing members <BR>
<U>Do not</U> let them lose their respect for you. </LI>
<U><LI>Do</U> write clear reports on a regular/weekly basis to your Wing <BR>
<U>Do not</U> forget to BCC </FONT><A HREF="mailto:reports@thebhg.org"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#ffffff">reports@thebhg.org</FONT></A><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#ffffff"> on all reports and the JUD on all other Wing emails. </LI>
<U><LI>Do</U> award IC's for good/regular Wing work. <BR>
<U>Do not</U> award them too often, as they will lose their value to the hunters. </LI>
<U><LI>Do</U> run decent competitive events in your Wing <BR>
<U>Do not</U> make them too easy just to help your hunters climb the ranks </LI>
<U><LI>Do</U> keep in contact with your Wing with additional emails as well as your reports <BR>
<U>Do not</U> spam their inbox with too many emails. </LI>
<U><LI>Do</U> send a recommendation to the JUD of your successor if you chose to step down. <BR>
<U>Do not</U> appoint them yourself in your leaving email to the Wing.</LI></OL>


<P>Well, now you can see that being a WARD is quite an involved job, but considering you are already reading this, and have been placed in the position of WARD it shows that the Commission have faith in you. And we know that you can take on this task and really make something of your Kabal. So good luck to you and may your Kabal Prosper.</P>
